channel.title: Hmm quick question
channel.description:
how do i know when my server is running because my server atm only says
Starting Cheezscape server on 0.0.0.0:43594
is that mean its running or does it say something else when it starts running?

item.title: Hmm quick question
item.dc:creator: @Khasck Khasck
item.description:
@Khasck wrote:

only online to himself, if he doesnt have himachi or no-ip, its not going to be open to everyone.
but to just get on your server, click runserver.bat and open up moparscape, type in your login info, and leave the Server IP address blank, and try logging in, if you cant, then theres a error with your coding, or you didnt run the server right,

-Will

item.title: Hmm quick question
item.dc:creator: @Tico135 Tico
item.description:
@Tico135 wrote:

[quote=“zezimamo, post:1, topic:92866”]how do i know when my server is running because my server atm only says

Starting Cheezscape server on 0.0.0.0:43594

is that mean its running or does it say something else when it starts running?[/quote]

This means that your server IS running and online. Try to log in and it should work.

Tico135

item.title: Hmm quick question
item.dc:creator: @Khasck Khasck
item.description:
@Khasck wrote:

even tho that means its running, it doesnt mean its online.
you need to compile the server, to make sure theres no errors, and you also need a himachi, or no-ip to make it online to everyone, not just yourself.

-Will
